channel.title: Proxy Rotations
channel.description: I noticed that in pplsuqbawlz's stickied ridicule of some random nub he mentioned 'proxy rotations'. I have a fully working random brute-forcer, except for the fact that it gets beaten down every 6 tries.. so I was wondering if anyone could point me in the right direction? As far as I know all you'd need is a hashtable of several different SOCK5 proxies, but I have no idea how to plug your IP address directly in via Java. Help appreciated, thanks.
